subSubSection.paragraph:
Genitalia . (
Fig. 2
). Pygofer black dorsally, including beak; pale brown laterally and along posterior margin towards dorsal beak; in ventral view outline, sub-rectangular with flattened anterior margin; dorsal beak in lateral view sharply defined and relatively long; upper lobes short, acutely rounded apically; basal lobes in ventral view moderately long, with narrowed rounded termination; claspers in lateral view strongly elongated, bluntly rounded apically, extending well beyond pygofer margins; uncus in lateral view much shorter than claspers, acutely rounded apically; pseudoparameres clearly longer than endotheca.
